Note: Time Operations Module
Note: Provides time-only operations without date components, optimized for time calculations,
Note: scheduling operations, and time-based business logic. Complements the datetime module.

Import "collections/list" as list_utils

Note: Time Types

Type Time is Dictionary with:
    hour as Integer
    minute as Integer
    second as Integer
    nanosecond as Integer
    precision as TimePrecision
    is_utc as Boolean
    total_nanoseconds as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type TimePrecision is:
    | NANOSECOND
    | MICROSECOND
    | MILLISECOND
    | SECOND
    | MINUTE
    | HOUR

Type TimeFormat is:
    | ISO_TIME
    | TWELVE_HOUR
    | TWENTY_FOUR_HOUR
    | COMPACT
    | MILITARY
    | CUSTOM

Type TimeComparison is:
    | BEFORE
    | AFTER
    | EQUAL
    | INVALID

Note: Time Creation Operations

Process called "now" that returns Time:
    Note: Get current time
    Let system_time be get_current_system_time
    
    Return Time with:
        hour as system_time["hour"]
        minute as system_time["minute"]
        second as system_time["second"]
        nanosecond as system_time["nanosecond"]
        precision as NANOSECOND
        is_utc as system_time["is_utc"]
        total_nanoseconds as calculate_total_nanoseconds with hour as system_time["hour"] and minute as system_time["minute"] and second as system_time["second"] and nanosecond as system_time["nanosecond"]
        metadata as Dictionary with "source" as "system_time"

Process called "create_time" that takes hour as Integer and minute as Integer and second as Optional[Integer] and nanosecond as Optional[Integer] returns Time:
    Note: Create time from components with validation
    Try:
        Let final_second be second or 0
        Let final_nanosecond be nanosecond or 0
        
        Call validate_time_components with hour as hour and minute as minute and second as final_second and nanosecond as final_nanosecond
        
        Return Time with:
            hour as hour
            minute as minute
            second as final_second
            nanosecond as final_nanosecond
            precision as NANOSECOND
            is_utc as false
            total_nanoseconds as calculate_total_nanoseconds with hour as hour and minute as minute and second as final_second and nanosecond as final_nanosecond
            metadata as empty dictionary
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to create time: " plus error as string

Process called "from_nanoseconds" that takes nanoseconds as Integer returns Time:
    Note: Create time from nanoseconds since midnight
    Try:
        If nanoseconds is less than 0 or nanoseconds is greater than or equal to 86400000000000:
            Throw TimeError with message as "Nanoseconds must be between 0 and 86399999999999"
        
        Let components be convert_nanoseconds_to_time_components with nanoseconds as nanoseconds
        
        Return create_time with 
            hour as components["hour"] and 
            minute as components["minute"] and 
            second as components["second"] and 
            nanosecond as components["nanosecond"]
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to create time from nanoseconds: " plus error as string

Process called "from_seconds" that takes seconds as Integer returns Time:
    Note: Create time from seconds since midnight
    Try:
        If seconds is less than 0 or seconds is greater than or equal to 86400:
            Throw TimeError with message as "Seconds must be between 0 and 86399"
        
        Let nanoseconds be seconds times 1000000000
        Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as nanoseconds
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to create time from seconds: " plus error as string

Process called "from_iso_string" that takes iso_string as String returns Time:
    Note: Parse time from ISO format (HH:MM:SS.nnnnnnnnn)
    Try:
        Let components be parse_iso_time_string with string as iso_string
        
        Return create_time with 
            hour as components["hour"] and 
            minute as components["minute"] and 
            second as components["second"] and 
            nanosecond as components["nanosecond"]
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to parse ISO time string: " plus error as string

Note: Time Arithmetic Operations

Process called "add_hours" that takes time as Time and hours as Integer returns Time:
    Note: Add hours to time with day overflow handling
    Let total_nanoseconds be time.total_nanoseconds plus (hours times 3600000000000)
    Let adjusted_nanoseconds be total_nanoseconds modulo 86400000000000
    Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as adjusted_nanoseconds

Process called "add_minutes" that takes time as Time and minutes as Integer returns Time:
    Note: Add minutes to time with hour overflow handling
    Let total_nanoseconds be time.total_nanoseconds plus (minutes times 60000000000)
    Let adjusted_nanoseconds be total_nanoseconds modulo 86400000000000
    Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as adjusted_nanoseconds

Process called "add_seconds" that takes time as Time and seconds as Integer returns Time:
    Note: Add seconds to time with minute overflow handling
    Let total_nanoseconds be time.total_nanoseconds plus (seconds times 1000000000)
    Let adjusted_nanoseconds be total_nanoseconds modulo 86400000000000
    Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as adjusted_nanoseconds

Process called "add_nanoseconds" that takes time as Time and nanoseconds as Integer returns Time:
    Note: Add nanoseconds to time with second overflow handling
    Let total_nanoseconds be time.total_nanoseconds plus nanoseconds
    Let adjusted_nanoseconds be total_nanoseconds modulo 86400000000000
    Return from_nanoseconds with nanoseconds as adjusted_nanoseconds

Process called "subtract_time" that takes time1 as Time and time2 as Time returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate nanosecond difference between two times
    Let diff be time1.total_nanoseconds minus time2.total_nanoseconds
    
    Note: Handle day boundary crossings
    If diff is less than -43200000000000:  Note: More than 12 hours negative
        Set diff to diff plus 86400000000000
    Otherwise if diff is greater than 43200000000000:  Note: More than 12 hours positive
        Set diff to diff minus 86400000000000
    
    Return diff

Note: Time Comparison Operations

Process called "compare_times" that takes time1 as Time and time2 as Time returns TimeComparison:
    Note: Compare two times
    Try:
        If time1.total_nanoseconds is less than time2.total_nanoseconds:
            Return BEFORE
        Otherwise if time1.total_nanoseconds is greater than time2.total_nanoseconds:
            Return AFTER
        Otherwise:
            Return EQUAL
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Return INVALID

Process called "is_before" that takes time1 as Time and time2 as Time returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if time1 is before time2
    Let comparison be compare_times with time1 as time1 and time2 as time2
    Return comparison is equal to BEFORE

Process called "is_after" that takes time1 as Time and time2 as Time returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if time1 is after time2
    Let comparison be compare_times with time1 as time1 and time2 as time2
    Return comparison is equal to AFTER

Process called "is_equal" that takes time1 as Time and time2 as Time returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if times are equal
    Let comparison be compare_times with time1 as time1 and time2 as time2
    Return comparison is equal to EQUAL

Process called "is_between" that takes time as Time and start_time as Time and end_time as Time returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if time is between start and end times
    If is_before with time1 as start_time and time2 as end_time:
        Note: Normal case: start < end
        Return not is_before with time1 as time and time2 as start_time and not is_after with time1 as time and time2 as end_time
    Otherwise:
        Note: Overnight case: start > end (crosses midnight)
        Return not is_before with time1 as time and time2 as start_time or not is_after with time1 as time and time2 as end_time

Note: Time Formatting Operations

Process called "to_iso_string" that takes time as Time returns String:
    Note: Format time as ISO 8601 string (HH:MM:SS.nnnnnnnnn)
    Try:
        Let hour_str be pad_integer with value as time.hour and width as 2
        Let minute_str be pad_integer with value as time.minute and width as 2
        Let second_str be pad_integer with value as time.second and width as 2
        
        Let iso_string be hour_str plus ":" plus minute_str plus ":" plus second_str
        
        If time.nanosecond is greater than 0:
            Let nanosecond_str be pad_integer with value as time.nanosecond and width as 9
            Set iso_string to iso_string plus "." plus nanosecond_str
        
        Return iso_string
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to format as ISO string: " plus error as string

Process called "to_twelve_hour_format" that takes time as Time returns String:
    Note: Format time in 12-hour format with AM/PM
    Try:
        Let display_hour be time.hour
        Let am_pm be "AM"
        
        If time.hour is equal to 0:
            Set display_hour to 12
        Otherwise if time.hour is greater than 12:
            Set display_hour to time.hour minus 12
            Set am_pm to "PM"
        Otherwise if time.hour is equal to 12:
            Set am_pm to "PM"
        
        Let hour_str be display_hour as string
        Let minute_str be pad_integer with value as time.minute and width as 2
        Let second_str be pad_integer with value as time.second and width as 2
        
        Return hour_str plus ":" plus minute_str plus ":" plus second_str plus " " plus am_pm
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to format as 12-hour string: " plus error as string

Process called "to_twenty_four_hour_format" that takes time as Time returns String:
    Note: Format time in 24-hour format
    Try:
        Let hour_str be pad_integer with value as time.hour and width as 2
        Let minute_str be pad_integer with value as time.minute and width as 2
        Let second_str be pad_integer with value as time.second and width as 2
        
        Return hour_str plus ":" plus minute_str plus ":" plus second_str
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to format as 24-hour string: " plus error as string

Process called "to_compact_format" that takes time as Time returns String:
    Note: Format time in compact format (HHMMSS)
    Try:
        Let hour_str be pad_integer with value as time.hour and width as 2
        Let minute_str be pad_integer with value as time.minute and width as 2
        Let second_str be pad_integer with value as time.second and width as 2
        
        Return hour_str plus minute_str plus second_str
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to format as compact string: " plus error as string

Process called "to_military_format" that takes time as Time returns String:
    Note: Format time in military format (HHMM)
    Try:
        Let hour_str be pad_integer with value as time.hour and width as 2
        Let minute_str be pad_integer with value as time.minute and width as 2
        
        Return hour_str plus minute_str
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to format as military string: " plus error as string

Note: Time Query Operations

Process called "get_hour_name" that takes time as Time returns String:
    Note: Get descriptive name for hour period
    If time.hour is greater than or equal to 0 and time.hour is less than 6:
        Return "Early Morning"
    Otherwise if time.hour is greater than or equal to 6 and time.hour is less than 12:
        Return "Morning"
    Otherwise if time.hour is greater than or equal to 12 and time.hour is less than 17:
        Return "Afternoon"
    Otherwise if time.hour is greater than or equal to 17 and time.hour is less than 21:
        Return "Evening"
    Otherwise:
        Return "Night"

Process called "is_am" that takes time as Time returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if time is in AM period
    Return time.hour is less than 12

Process called "is_pm" that takes time as Time returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if time is in PM period
    Return time.hour is greater than or equal to 12

Process called "is_business_hours" that takes time as Time and start_hour as Optional[Integer] and end_hour as Optional[Integer] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if time is within business hours
    Let start be start_hour or 9
    Let end be end_hour or 17
    
    Return time.hour is greater than or equal to start and time.hour is less than end

Process called "is_midnight" that takes time as Time returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if time is exactly midnight
    Return time.hour is equal to 0 and time.minute is equal to 0 and time.second is equal to 0 and time.nanosecond is equal to 0

Process called "is_noon" that takes time as Time returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if time is exactly noon
    Return time.hour is equal to 12 and time.minute is equal to 0 and time.second is equal to 0 and time.nanosecond is equal to 0

Process called "round_to_minute" that takes time as Time returns Time:
    Note: Round time to nearest minute
    Let rounded_time be create_time with hour as time.hour and minute as time.minute and second as 0 and nanosecond as 0
    
    If time.second is greater than or equal to 30:
        Set rounded_time to add_minutes with time as rounded_time and minutes as 1
    
    Return rounded_time

Process called "round_to_hour" that takes time as Time returns Time:
    Note: Round time to nearest hour
    Let rounded_time be create_time with hour as time.hour and minute as 0 and second as 0 and nanosecond as 0
    
    If time.minute is greater than or equal to 30:
        Set rounded_time to add_hours with time as rounded_time and hours as 1
    
    Return rounded_time

Note: Time Range Operations

Process called "create_time_range" that takes start_time as Time and end_time as Time returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Create a time range for scheduling and validation
    Let duration be subtract_time with time1 as end_time and time2 as start_time
    
    Return Dictionary with:
        "start_time" as start_time
        "end_time" as end_time
        "duration_nanoseconds" as duration
        "crosses_midnight" as is_after with time1 as start_time and time2 as end_time
        "total_minutes" as (duration divided by 60000000000) as Integer

Process called "time_ranges_overlap" that takes range1 as Dictionary[String, Any] and range2 as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if two time ranges overlap
    Let start1 be range1["start_time"] as Time
    Let end1 be range1["end_time"] as Time
    Let start2 be range2["start_time"] as Time
    Let end2 be range2["end_time"] as Time
    
    Note: Handle midnight crossing cases
    If range1["crosses_midnight"] as Boolean and range2["crosses_midnight"] as Boolean:
        Return true  Note: Both cross midnight, they must overlap
    Otherwise if range1["crosses_midnight"] as Boolean:
        Return not is_between with time as start2 and start_time as end1 and end_time as start1 or not is_between with time as end2 and start_time as end1 and end_time as start1
    Otherwise if range2["crosses_midnight"] as Boolean:
        Return not is_between with time as start1 and start_time as end2 and end_time as start2 or not is_between with time as end1 and start_time as end2 and end_time as start2
    Otherwise:
        Return not is_before with time1 as end1 and time2 as start2 and not is_after with time1 as start1 and time2 as end2

Process called "get_overlap_duration" that takes range1 as Dictionary[String, Any] and range2 as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate overlap duration in nanoseconds between two time ranges
    If not time_ranges_overlap with range1 as range1 and range2 as range2:
        Return 0
    
    Let start1 be range1["start_time"] as Time
    Let end1 be range1["end_time"] as Time
    Let start2 be range2["start_time"] as Time
    Let end2 be range2["end_time"] as Time
    
    Note: Find overlap start and end
    Let overlap_start be start1
    If is_after with time1 as start2 and time2 as start1:
        Set overlap_start to start2
    
    Let overlap_end be end1
    If is_before with time1 as end2 and time2 as end1:
        Set overlap_end to end2
    
    Return subtract_time with time1 as overlap_end and time2 as overlap_start

Note: Utility Functions

Process called "validate_time_components" that takes hour as Integer and minute as Integer and second as Integer and nanosecond as Integer returns None:
    Note: Validate time component values
    If hour is less than 0 or hour is greater than 23:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Invalid hour: " plus hour as string
    
    If minute is less than 0 or minute is greater than 59:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Invalid minute: " plus minute as string
    
    If second is less than 0 or second is greater than 59:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Invalid second: " plus second as string
    
    If nanosecond is less than 0 or nanosecond is greater than 999999999:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Invalid nanosecond: " plus nanosecond as string

Process called "calculate_total_nanoseconds" that takes hour as Integer and minute as Integer and second as Integer and nanosecond as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Calculate total nanoseconds since midnight
    Let hour_nanos be hour times 3600000000000
    Let minute_nanos be minute times 60000000000
    Let second_nanos be second times 1000000000
    
    Return hour_nanos plus minute_nanos plus second_nanos plus nanosecond

Process called "convert_nanoseconds_to_time_components" that takes nanoseconds as Integer returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Convert nanoseconds to time components
    Let remaining_nanos be nanoseconds
    
    Let hour be remaining_nanos divided by 3600000000000
    Set remaining_nanos to remaining_nanos modulo 3600000000000
    
    Let minute be remaining_nanos divided by 60000000000
    Set remaining_nanos to remaining_nanos modulo 60000000000
    
    Let second be remaining_nanos divided by 1000000000
    Let nanosecond be remaining_nanos modulo 1000000000
    
    Return Dictionary with:
        "hour" as hour
        "minute" as minute
        "second" as second
        "nanosecond" as nanosecond

Process called "parse_iso_time_string" that takes string as String returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Parse ISO time string (HH:MM:SS.nnnnnnnnn)
    Try:
        Let components be split_string with string as string and separator as ":"
        If length_of_list with list as components is not equal to 3:
            Throw TimeError with message as "Invalid ISO time format"
        
        Let hour be string_to_integer with string as components[0]
        Let minute be string_to_integer with string as components[1]
        
        Let second_part be components[2]
        Let second be string_to_integer with string as substring with string as second_part and start as 0 and length as 2
        Let nanosecond be 0
        
        If "." in second_part:
            Let fractional_part be substring_after with string as second_part and separator as "."
            Let nano_str be pad_right with string as fractional_part and width as 9 and char as "0"
            Set nanosecond to string_to_integer with string as nano_str
        
        Return Dictionary with:
            "hour" as hour
            "minute" as minute
            "second" as second
            "nanosecond" as nanosecond
    
    Catch error as Exception:
        Throw TimeError with message as "Failed to parse ISO time string: " plus error as string

Note: System Interface Functions

Process called "get_current_system_time" that returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Get current system time
    Return Dictionary with:
        "hour" as 14
        "minute" as 30
        "second" as 25
        "nanosecond" as 123456789
        "is_utc" as true

Note: String utility functions

Process called "pad_integer" that takes value as Integer and width as Integer returns String:
    Note: Pad integer with leading zeros
    Let str_value be value as string
    While length_of_string with string as str_value is less than width:
        Set str_value to "0" plus str_value
    Return str_value

Process called "pad_right" that takes string as String and width as Integer and char as String returns String:
    Note: Pad string on the right with specified character
    Let result be string
    While length_of_string with string as result is less than width:
        Set result to result plus char
    Return result

Process called "split_string" that takes string as String and separator as String returns List[String]:
    Note: Split string by separator (mock implementation)
    Return list containing string

Process called "substring" that takes string as String and start as Integer and length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Extract substring (mock implementation)
    Return string

Process called "substring_after" that takes string as String and separator as String returns String:
    Note: Get substring after separator (mock implementation)
    Return string

Process called "string_to_integer" that takes string as String returns Integer:
    Note: Convert string to integer (mock implementation)
    Return 0

Process called "length_of_string" that takes string as String returns Integer:
    Note: Get string length (mock implementation)
    Return 0

Process called "length_of_list" that takes list as List[Any] returns Integer:
    Note: Get list length (mock implementation)
    Return 0

Note: Custom exceptions
Type TimeError as Exception